The '''Meister Eckhart Prize''' is a biannual award consisting of a prize of €50,000 given to "thinkers who produce high-quality work on the subject of [[identity (social science)|identity]]" by the ''Identity Foundation''. The prize is named after [[Meister Eckhart]] (1260–1328), a German [[theology|theologian]], [[philosopher]] and [[mysticism|mystic]].
==Award recipients== * 2001: [[Richard Rorty]]<ref>{{cite news |first=David |last=Lauer |title=Ein leicht surrealer Effekt |url=http://www.taz.de/index.php?id=archivseite&dig=2001/12/05/a0143 |publisher=[[die tageszeitung]] |language=German |date=2001-12-05 |accessdate=2008-05-03 }}</ref> * 2003: [[Claude Lévi-Strauss]] * 2005: [[Ernst Tugendhat]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Meister-Eckhart-Preis für Ernst Tugendhat |url=http://www.abendblatt.de/daten/2005/11/18/504476.html |publisher=[[Hamburger Abendblatt]] |language=German |date=2005-11-18 |accessdate=2008-05-03 }}</ref> * 2007: [[Amartya Sen]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Meister-Eckhart-Preis für Amartya Sen |url=http://www.boersenblatt.net/152011/ |publisher=Börsenblatt Online |language=German |date=2007-07-25 |accessdate=2008-05-03 }}</ref> * 2009: [[Amitai Etzioni]] * 2012: [[Michel Serres]] * 2014: [[Seyla Benhabib]]
